    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1974-05-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1974-05-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="50"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                <head>50. National Security Study Memorandum 202<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d50fn1">
                        <p>
                            <seg type="summary">Summary: President <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1"
                                    >Nixon</persName> directed the National Security Council Under
                                Secretaries Committee to review <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss>
                                policy concerning the Nonproliferation Treaty.</seg>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <seg type="source">Source: National Archives, Nixon Presidential
                                Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, Institutional
                                Files, National Security Study Memoranda, Box H–205, <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss> 202. Secret. <persName
                                    corresp="#p_SBA_1">Scowcroft</persName> signed for <persName
                                    corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> above <persName
                                    corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>’s typed signature.
                                Copies were sent to <persName corresp="#p_RKW_1">Rush</persName> and
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MTH_1">Moorer</persName>. <persName
                                    corresp="#p_SBA_1">Scowcroft</persName> underlined the date in
                                the last paragraph of the memorandum and placed a vertical line in
                                the left-hand margin next to that sentence. <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss> 13 is published in <ref
                                    target="frus1969-76ve02#d9">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, volume E–2,
                                    Documents on Arms Control and Nonproliferation, 1969–1972, as
                                    Document 9</ref>. The study prepared in response to <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss> 13 is ibid., <ref
                                    target="frus1969-76ve02#d13">Document 13</ref>. <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss> 195 is <ref
                                    target="frus1969-76ve02#d30">Document 30</ref> in this volume.
                                    <gloss target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss> 156 is published in <ref
                                    target="frus1969-76ve07#d275">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, volume E–7,
                                    Documents on South Asia, 1969–1972, as Document 275</ref>. A
                                draft of the report detailing the study’s findings study is <ref
                                    target="frus1969-76ve07#d57">Document 57</ref> in this
                                volume.</seg>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1974-05-23"
                        >May 23, 1974</date>.</dateline>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Deputy Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Director, Arms Control and Disarmament Agency</item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                    <item>The Chairman, Atomic Energy Commission</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has directed a review of <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss>
                    policy concerning the nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (<gloss target="#t_NPT_1"
                        >NPT</gloss>).</p>
                <p>The study should review present <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> policy
                    concerning non-proliferation and the <gloss target="#t_NPT_1">NPT</gloss> in the
                    light of changed conditions since completion of <gloss target="#t_NSSM_1"
                        >NSSM</gloss> 13, and, in particular, in light of India’s announcement of
                    its underground nuclear test. The study should consider the full range of issues
                    posed by the changed circumstances affecting our posture toward
                    non-proliferation and the <gloss target="#t_NPT_1">NPT</gloss> and present
                    options for future <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> policy. It also should
                    consider specifically whether the <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss> should
                    press for renewed support for the treaty by those now party to it and accession
                    to the treaty by those not yet signators, and if so how and to what extent. The
                    options should include consideration of public, congressional and diplomatic
                    posture for the <gloss target="#t_US_1">U.S.</gloss>
                </p>
                <p>The study should take into account the study done in response to <gloss
                        target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss> 13 and subsequent work in connection
                    therewith, particularly that in preparation for the 1975 <gloss
                        target="#t_NPT_1">NPT</gloss> Review Conference. It also should take into
                    account the work done in connection with <gloss target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss>
                    195 and the updating currently underway in connection with <gloss
                        target="#t_NSSM_1">NSSM</gloss> 156.</p>
                <pb facs="0146" n="112" xml:id="pg_112"/>
                <p>The President has directed that the study be accomplished by the <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Under Secretaries Committee and be forwarded
                    not later than June 12, 1974.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_KHA_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
